# SaveT Site Structure

## Subpage routing

SaveT URLs are **not** in a `savet/` content folder. Use root-level files with explicit `permalink`:

| Page | File | URL |
|------|------|-----|
| Main | `savet.md` | `/savet/` |
| Roadmap | `savet-roadmap.html` | `/savet/roadmap/` |
| Privacy | `savet-legal-privacy.html` | `/savet/legal/privacy/` |
| Terms | `savet-legal-terms.html` | `/savet/legal/terms/` |

When adding a new SaveT subpage, also update `sitemap.xml`.

## Roadmap page

- **Layout:** `_layouts/savet-roadmap.html` with `bodyClass: page-savet page-savet-roadmap`
- **Front matter:** `canva_embed_url`, `canva_view_url`, `canva_title`, `canva_author` drive the embed and attribution
- **Styles:** scoped under `.page-savet-roadmap` in `_sass/pages/_page-savet.scss` (`.savet-canva-wrap`, `.savet-canva-attribution`)
- **Embed ratio:** portrait `aspect-ratio: 100 / 141.4286`; move Canva inline styles into SCSS, not raw HTML
- **Copy:** page hero/lead/CTAs in English; Canva attribution text as set in front matter

## Navigation

Roadmap is linked from `/savet/` **hero CTA only** (`cta` in `savet.md` front matter). Do not add a footer link for roadmap. Not in main nav (`_data/menus.yml`) unless explicitly requested.
